There's a couple of ways
you could write this out.

00:03:06.100 --> 00:03:09.827
This is equivalent to,
this is equivalent to

00:03:09.827 --> 00:03:15.466
the probability, probability of A given B.

00:03:16.167 --> 00:03:21.466
Given B, times the probability of B.

00:03:21.500 --> 00:03:22.734
And hopefully that makes sense.

00:03:22.900 --> 00:03:25.100
The probability that B happens and that

00:03:25.100 --> 00:03:26.900
given that B had happened, the probability

00:03:26.900 --> 00:03:28.200
that A happens.

00:03:28.433 --> 00:03:30.466
And that would also be equal to ...

00:03:30.701 --> 00:03:32.833
So obviously this is A and B is happening,

00:03:32.833 --> 00:03:34.500
or you could do it the other way around.

00:03:34.500 --> 00:03:36.767
You could view it as
the probability that B,

00:03:36.767 --> 00:03:42.133
the probability that B given A happens.

00:03:42.701 --> 00:03:47.600
Given A happens, times
the probability of A.

00:03:48.330 --> 00:03:50.833
Times the probability of A.

00:03:50.833 --> 00:03:51.766
This also makes sense.

